elements.2211.03165_70d5b8def83a4a47746f23a199b19: Deep motion forecasting models have achieved great success when trained on a massive amount of data
elements.2211.03165_1dbd989eba00b6a6e1022f115e13a: Yet, they often perform poorly when training data is limited
elements.2211.03165_a1b99596903fb1c3533e5e3c351a4: To address this challenge, we propose a transfer learning approach for efficiently adapting pre-trained forecasting models to new domains, such as unseen agent types and scene contexts
elements.2211.03165_2fa01eab14dfa7fd070c45bb532b2: Unlike the conventional fine-tuning approach that updates the whole encoder, our main idea is to reduce the amount of tunable parameters that can precisely account for the target domain-specific motion style
elements.2211.03165_22bd776c4f6e786336759c7f944d4: To this end, we introduce two components that exploit our prior knowledge of motion style shifts: (i) a low-rank motion style adapter that projects and adjusts the style features at a low-dimensional bottleneck; and (ii) a modular adapter strategy that disentangles the features of scene context and motion history to facilitate a fine-grained choice of adaptation layers
elements.2211.03165_89f4189377c960fa87e42bfbae845: Through extensive experimentation, we show that our proposed adapter design, coined MoSA, outperforms prior methods on several forecasting benchmarks
elements.2211.03165_122bf23f4f21890c78a1f454581c7: Motion forecasting is an essential pillar for the successful deployment of autonomous systems in environments comprising various heterogeneous agents
elements.2211.03165_27a50db59172a5454cf0c0b679bcf: It presents the challenges of modeling (i) universal etiquette (
elements.2211.03165_3f19b3fd14879075103c958b5daed: , goal-directed behaviors, avoiding collisions) that govern general motion dynamics of all agents; and (ii) social norms (
elements.2211.03165_58630a5fa73cf469f0ddb1297eebb: , the minimum separation distance, preferred speed) that influence the navigation styles of different agents across different locations
elements.2211.03165_6fa66e5e0a832d9711077a6cc3060: Owing to the success of deep neural networks on large-scale datasets, learning prediction models in a data-driven manner has become a de-facto approach for motion forecasting and has shown impressive results
elements.2211.03165_22c84306a4c862a2d2fd59c556a97: However, existing deep forecasting models suffer from inferior performance when they encounter novel scenarios
elements.2211.03165_a6420cb56453f61a3838a69bda19e: For instance, a network trained with large-scale data for pedestrian forecasting struggles to directly generalize to cyclists
elements.2211.03165_d76f358ef98f83674aef60be0007d: Some recent methods propose to incorporate strong priors robust to the underlying distribution shifts
elements.2211.03165_854b55f7e0fa163c0e0514215f54c: Yet, these priors often make strong assumptions on the distribution shifts, which may not hold in practice
elements.2211.03165_71f4083c69902ff20aeb7b93d797a: This shortcoming motivates the following transfer learning paradigm: adapting a forecasting model pretrained on one domain with sufficient data to new domains such as unseen agent types and scene contexts
elements.2211.03165_f65c5c41f832392c38965ee0d5bf7: One common transfer learning approach is fine-tuning a pretrained model on the data collected from target domain
elements.2211.03165_f69c49d946b734e6ad69cdf1a271a: However, directly updating the model is often sample inefficient, as it fails to exploit the inherent structure of the distributional shifts in the motion context
elements.2211.03165_d5ff6fef77fbe08e7be64bd55a15e: In the forecasting setup, the physical laws behind motion dynamics are generally invariant across geographical locations and agent types: all agents move towards their goal and avoid collisions
elements.2211.03165_a7be78040fbfb64ae9fc513eb5a6b: As a result, the distribution shift can be largely attributed to the changes in the motion style, defined as the way an agent interacts with its surroundings
elements.2211.03165_f4f3d0a8940279a9de1db173c6524: Given this decoupling of motion dynamics, it can be efficient for an adaptation algorithm to only account for the updates in the target motion style.
elements.2211.03165_05ff51979ec4148ce6d3d0bf604aa: In this work, we efficiently adapt a deep forecasting model from one motion style to another
